  card: {
    question: "<p>Using the <code>::before</code> and <code>::after</code> selectors, what does the following CSS code do?</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-css\">div::before {\n   content: 'Hello!';\n   color: white;\n}\ndiv::after {\n   content: 'Goodbye!';\n   color: black;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>???</p>\n",
    answers: [
      {
        text: 'Adds a white Hello! before every div element with a black Goodbye! after.',
      },
      {
        text: 'Adds a white Hello! after every div element with a black Goodbye! before.',
      },
      {
        text: 'It does nothing, improper CSS.',
      },
    ],
    comment: '<p>Use the <code>::before</code> selector to add and style content just before the first child of an element.\nSimilarly, use the <code>::after</code> selector to add and style content after the last child of the element.</p>\n<p>Consider the following HTML code:</p>\n<pre><code class="language-html">  &#x3C;p>First&#x3C;/p>\n  &#x3C;p>Second&#x3C;/p>\n  &#x3C;p>Third&#x3C;/p>\n</code></pre>\n<p>And the following CSS snippet:</p>\n<pre><code class="language-css">  p::before{\n    content: \'#\';\n    color: red;\n  }\n\n  p::after{\n    content: \'?\';\n    color: aqua;\n  }\n</code></pre>\n<p>This adds a red <strong>#</strong> at the start of every <code>p</code> element and a blue <strong>?</strong> at the end of them.</p>\n<p><svg height="auto" viewBox="0 0 800 300" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" version="1.2" baseProfile="tiny"><desc>Created by HiQPdf</desc><g fill="none" stroke="#000" fill-rule="evenodd" stroke-linecap="square" stroke-linejoin="bevel"><path d="M8 8h800v300H8V8" fill="#596193" stroke="none"/><text stroke="none" x="362" y="63" font-family="Arial" font-size="30" font-weight="400" fill="#ff4500">#</text><text stroke="none" x="379" y="63" font-family="Arial" font-size="30" font-weight="400" fill="#fff">First</text><text stroke="none" x="437" y="63" font-family="Arial" font-size="30" font-weight="400" fill="#0ff">?</text><text stroke="none" x="340.5" y="153" font-family="Arial" font-size="30" font-weight="400" fill="#ff4500">#</text><text stroke="none" x="357.5" y="153" font-family="Arial" font-size="30" font-weight="400" fill="#fff">Second</text><text stroke="none" x="458.5" y="153" font-family="Arial" font-size="30" font-weight="400" fill="#0ff">?</text><text stroke="none" x="356" y="243" font-family="Arial" font-size="30" font-weight="400" fill="#ff4500">#</text><text stroke="none" x="373" y="243" font-family="Arial" font-size="30" font-weight="400" fill="#fff">Third</text><text stroke="none" x="443" y="243" font-family="Arial" font-size="30" font-weight="400" fill="#0ff">?</text></g></svg></p>\n<p><code>content</code> is mandatory to display the element but can be empty (<code>content:"";</code>).</p>\n<p>Both <code>::before</code> and <code>::after</code> can be used to display shapes, images or even borders.</p>\n',
  },
